<br>
It's not an EQ killer yet, of that I am sure. Yes, some of you are screaming now about how it's so awsome and so on. So far it doesn't look like an EQ killer to me. There isn't enough of that 'magic something' that makes me drool and want to play compulsively. Add to that how many people had not bad experiences with the original AC but just plain boring ones and whipping people up into a frenzy over the sequel will be a bit harder. If they make certain changes to loging in (@#$%! @#$%!) and make the game more easy to get into and add decent documentation I'll most likely give it a go.<br>
<br>
I think EQ will be around for a few more years. I believe it is starting to wind down a bit though. WoW and SWG are the biggest upcoming games in my opinion. Sorry SB fans but I don't think your game of choice is going to be the EQ killer due to the pvp involved. Say what you will, the numbers are clear enough in that a majority of EQ's players don't want pvp. Don't blame me or start with how everyone would love a good pvp system and would love it if they just gave it a try. Be honest, you don't really want the Hugglez Treespirits of gaming diluting your game and blubiefying it anyway.<br>
<br>
