<br>
Another question is if a sci-fi MMOG will go well with the traditionally fantasy RPers? I know people who wouldn't touch AO just because it was sci-fi. They wanted the familiar elves, magic, and dragons. It's a highly known brand however but then being so highly known poses another problem in and of itself. That problem being hordes of gamers who don't play online games but really really love Star Wars and want to be a Jedi and save the galaxy!!! The game itself may quite easily turn out to be the best one of current MMOGs in development considering the massive experience the people working on the game must have by now from EQ. The players may quite easily turn it into an unbearable torment to play.<br>
<br>
